    {
      "id": "PopularPost317426",
      "post_content": "What about an alternative cost to putting the top card of your library in the ante for non-ante games? Since this card is so powerful, it must be somewhat punishing. I'm thinking we could change the rules definition of \"add to ante\" text for those old cards to something like:  \n  \n\"Random opponent gains ownership of this card until end of game. That player may play the card now for ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) or 2 life, otherwise they must add the card to their hand.\"  \n  \nMaybe a little complicated, but I like the mechanics of it... It still plays along with the original concept of ante cards... that your opponent gets the card. It's just that now we're looking at it in terms of them getting the card for this game only instead of for permanent ownership. It gives your opponent a really big chance of having a huge payoff. For a measly ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) if they have it, or 2 life if they don't, they can play whatever you gave them immediately... [Emrakul, the Aeons Torn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Emrakul, the Aeons Torn) anyone? Can you imagine your oppone... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Callahan09",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost317426\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">What about an alternative cost to putting the top card of your library in the ante for non-ante games?  Since this card is so powerful, it must be somewhat punishing.  I'm thinking we could change the rules definition of \"add to ante\" text for those old cards to something like:<br/><br/>\"Random opponent gains ownership of this card until end of game.  That player may play the card now for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> or 2 life, otherwise they must add the card to their hand.\"<br/><br/>Maybe a little complicated, but I like the mechanics of it... It still plays along with the original concept of ante cards... that your opponent gets the card.  It's just that now we're looking at it in terms of them getting the card for this game only instead of for permanent ownership.  It gives your opponent a really big chance of having a huge payoff.  For a measly <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> if they have it, or 2 life if they don't, they can play whatever you gave them immediately... <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Emrakul, the Aeons Torn\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Emrakul, the Aeons Torn\">Emrakul, the Aeons Torn</a> anyone?  Can you imagine your oppone... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 317426)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '317426'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy96189\">Callahan09</span>\r\n                                (5/23/2013 7:39:37 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
